, \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dave_Ellis_(saxophonist)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ourPrivacy notice\", \"from\": 480, \"to\": 497}, {\"ngram\": \"sport's constant quest\", \"from\": 501, \"to\": 523}, {\"ngram\": \"the perfect redemption arc\", \"from\": 528, \"to\": 554}, {\"ngram\": \"his happy ending\", \"from\": 579, \"to\": 595}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ellis has been a dominant force in paratriathlonfor nearly a decade but feared his career might be defined by the mechanical issue that forced him to withdraw three years ago in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 599, \"to\": 783, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 777, \"end\": 782, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9017212043779003, \"rank\": 0.10899020648514474, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ellis\", \"from\": 599, \"to\": 604}, {\"ngram\": \"a dominant force\", \"from\": 614, \"to\": 630}, {\"ngram\": \"his career\", \"from\": 678, \"to\": 688}, {\"ngram\": \"the mechanical issue\", \"from\": 709, \"to\": 729}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He did not even get a certificate for his troubles, after failing to finish the race.\", \"from\": 784, \"to\": 869, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a certificate\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 817}, {\"ngram\": \"his troubles\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 834}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 860, \"to\": 868}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Friends and family - in their red and blue T-shirts - watched anxiously as he and guide Luke Pollard gingerly made their way around the cobbled bike circuit and then cheered, through a mixture of relief and pride, as they dominated the run to win gold in the men's PTVI event.\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 1147, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 959, \"end\": 971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luke_Pollard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Luke Pollard\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luke_Pollard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luke_Pollard\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Friends\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 878}, {\"ngram\": \"family\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 889}, {\"ngram\": \"their red and blue T-shirts\", \"from\": 895, \"to\": 922}, {\"ngram\": \"their way\", \"from\": 986, \"to\": 995}, {\"ngram\": \"the cobbled bike circuit\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1027}, {\"ngram\": \"a mixture\", \"from\": 1054, \"to\": 1063}, {\"ngram\": \"relief\", \"from\": 1067, \"to\": 1073}, {\"ngram\": \"pride\", \"from\": 1078, \"to\": 1083}, {\"ngram\": \"the run\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1110}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1122}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's PTVI event\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1146}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was a tough couple of years after Tokyo, but it feels a bit unreal,\\\" said Ellis, who is one of over 1,000 elite athletes on UK Sport's National Lottery-funded World Class Programme, allowing them to train full time, have access to the world's best coaches and benefit from pioneering medical support - which has been vital on their pathway to theParis 2024Games.\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1515, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1187, \"end\": 1192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9017212043779003, \"rank\": 0.10899020648514474, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1227, \"end\": 1232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Havelock_Ellis\", \"score\": 0.7161617415830912, \"rank\": 0.3961674554284543, \"text\": \"Ellis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Havelock_Ellis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Havelock_Ellis\"}, {\"begin\": 1277, \"end\": 1285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 1277, \"end\": 1285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a tough couple\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1171}, {\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1180}, {\"ngram\": \"over 1,000 elite athletes\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1273}, {\"ngram\": \"access\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1380}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's best coaches\", \"from\": 1384, \"to\": 1408}, {\"ngram\": \"medical support\", \"from\": 1437, \"to\": 1452}, {\"ngram\": \"their pathway\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1492}, {\"ngram\": \"theParis\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1504}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You do not know how many Paralympic races you will get in your career, so that added extra nerves, and it just feels special to have pulled it off.\", \"from\": 1517, \"to\": 1665, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"how many Paralympic races\", \"from\": 1534, \"to\": 1559}, {\"ngram\": \"your career\", \"from\": 1576, \"to\": 1587}, {\"ngram\": \"extra nerves\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1615}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"After one lap of the bike I thought 'I have made it further than last time'.\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1744, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one lap\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1681}, {\"ngram\": \"the bike\", \"from\": 1685, \"to\": 1693}, {\"ngram\": \"last time\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1742}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not want to finish my career not even finishing a race at the Games.\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1819, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my career\", \"from\": 1770, \"to\": 1779}, {\"ngram\": \"a race\", \"from\": 1799, \"to\": 1805}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1809, \"to\": 1818}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was never any doubt I'd carry on and, if I can stay competitive, I'd love to keep on going too.\\\"\", \"from\": 1820, \"to\": 1922, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any doubt\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 1845}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ellis is not prone to exaggeration or superlatives.\", \"from\": 1924, \"to\": 1975, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ellis\", \"from\": 1924, \"to\": 1929}, {\"ngram\": \"exaggeration\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 1958}, {\"ngram\": \"superlatives\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 1974}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is - according to partner Claire Cashmore - a man of actions, not words.\", \"from\": 1976, \"to\": 2051, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"partner\", \"from\": 1997, \"to\": 2004}, {\"ngram\": \"a man\", \"from\": 2023, \"to\": 2028}, {\"ngram\": \"actions\", \"from\": 2032, \"to\": 2039}, {\"ngram\": \"words\", \"from\": 2045, \"to\": 2050}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She crossed the line in silver in the women's PTS5 event - British defending champion Lauren Steadman took bronze - and immediately asked where Ellis had finished.\", \"from\": 2053, \"to\": 2216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2112, \"end\": 2119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.7240693452993929, \"rank\": 0.37806079910445317, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 2139, \"end\": 2154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lauren_Steadman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lauren Steadman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lauren_Steadman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lauren_Steadman\"}, {\"begin\": 2197, \"end\": 2202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Havelock_Ellis\", \"score\": 0.7161617415830912, \"rank\": 0.3961674554284543, \"text\": \"Ellis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Havelock_Ellis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Havelock_Ellis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 2065, \"to\": 2073}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 2077, \"to\": 2083}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 2160, \"to\": 2166}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then came the tears.\", \"from\": 2217, \"to\": 2237, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the tears\", \"from\": 2227, \"to\": 2236}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Dave is the most determined, hardworking person I have ever met and he's finally he's got what he deserves, especially after Tokyo,\\\" said Cashmore, now a ten-time Paralympic medallist.\", \"from\": 2239, \"to\": 2424, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2365, \"end\": 2370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9017212043779003, \"rank\": 0.10899020648514474, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 2378, \"end\": 2386, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Cashmore_Ltd\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cashmore\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Cashmore_Ltd\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Cashmore_Ltd\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dave\", \"from\": 2240, \"to\": 2244}, {\"ngram\": \"now a ten-time Paralympic medallist\", \"from\": 2388, \"to\": 2423}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I felt so stressed not being able to watch him but I am so pleased he got his moment.\", \"from\": 2425, \"to\": 2511, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his moment\", \"from\": 2500, \"to\": 2510}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I can not tell you how resilient he is.\", \"from\": 2513, \"to\": 2553, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The work he does every day is inspiring and he deserves everything he gets.\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2629, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The work\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2562}, {\"ngram\": \"every day\", \"from\": 2571, \"to\": 2580}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 2610, \"to\": 2620}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's a man of few words, we are polar opposites in that respect.\\\"\", \"from\": 2630, \"to\": 2695, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a man\", \"from\": 2635, \"to\": 2640}, {\"ngram\": \"few words\", \"from\": 2644, \"to\": 2653}, {\"ngram\": \"polar opposites\", \"from\": 2662, \"to\": 2677}, {\"ngram\": \"that respect\", \"from\": 2681, \"to\": 2693}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When it comes to water quality in the Seine it seems you'd do well to bottle the best of British.\", \"from\": 2697, \"to\": 2794, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2735, \"end\": 2740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999909009603, \"rank\": 9.099104740182174e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 2786, \"end\": 2793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.7240693452993929, \"rank\": 0.37806079910445317, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"water quality\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2727}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WhereAlex Yee blazed a trailat the Olympics, Britain's Paralympic triathletes duly followed, winning two golds, a silver and two bronzes after a 24-hour delay to competition due to pollution concerns.\", \"from\": 2796, \"to\": 2996, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2841, \"end\": 2848, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9104671992351961, \"rank\": 0.09833676993299238, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WhereAlex Yee\", \"from\": 2796, \"to\": 2809}, {\"ngram\": \"a trailat\", \"from\": 2817, \"to\": 2826}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2827, \"to\": 2839}, {\"ngram\": \"two golds\", \"from\": 2897, \"to\": 2906}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver\", \"from\": 2908, \"to\": 2916}, {\"ngram\": \"two bronzes\", \"from\": 2921, \"to\": 2932}, {\"ngram\": \"a 24-hour delay\", \"from\": 2939, \"to\": 2954}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 2958, \"to\": 2969}, {\"ngram\": \"pollution concerns\", \"from\": 2977, \"to\": 2995}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the second consecutive morning they awoke unsure whether they'd compete, until the official with the dipstick gave the thumbs up.\", \"from\": 2998, \"to\": 3131, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the second consecutive morning\", \"from\": 3002, \"to\": 3032}, {\"ngram\": \"unsure\", \"from\": 3044, \"to\": 3050}, {\"ngram\": \"the official\", \"from\": 3081, \"to\": 3093}, {\"ngram\": \"the dipstick\", \"from\": 3099, \"to\": 3111}, {\"ngram\": \"the thumbs\", \"from\": 3117, \"to\": 3127}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If Ellis was a hot favourite in his race, few gave Megan Richter a chance in the women's PTS4 classification, her shock on crossing the line was, pardon the pun, duly off the scale.\", \"from\": 3133, \"to\": 3314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3136, \"end\": 3141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Havelock_Ellis\", \"score\": 0.7161617415830912, \"rank\": 0.3961674554284543, \"text\": \"Ellis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Havelock_Ellis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Have